        <div class="about-text">
            <h1>ABOUT<span>ME</span></h1>
            <h2>Wed Developer</h2>
             <p>As a beginner web developer, diving into the world of coding and creating websites can feel like stepping into a vast, unknown universe. Every line of code I write feels like a step forward, but I'm constantly aware of how much more there is to learn.
                One thing that's become clear to me early on is the importance of user experience. It's not just about making things look pretty (though that's part of it), but it's about creating websites that are intuitive and enjoyable for people to use.
                I've been experimenting with different projects, from simple personal websites to more complex web applications. With each project, I try to put myself in the shoes of the user. How easy is it to navigate? Are the buttons where they should be? Does the layout make sense?
                Getting feedback from others has been incredibly helpful. Whether it's friends and family or fellow developers in online communities, hearing what other people think of my work helps me see things from a different perspective. </p>
            <h2>Graphic designer</h2>
            <p>As a user engaging with graphic design, I find myself constantly drawn to captivating visuals that tell a story or convey a message effectively. Whether I'm browsing through a website, flipping through a magazine, or scrolling through social media, it's the designs that catch my eye and make me stop to take a closer look.
                One of the things I appreciate most about graphic design is its ability to evoke emotion and provoke thought. A well-designed logo can instantly communicate the essence of a brand, while a beautifully crafted infographic can make complex information easy to understand and digest. It's this power of visual communication that I find truly inspiring.
                As a user, I also value simplicity and clarity in design. A cluttered layout or overly complicated graphics can be overwhelming and off-putting. I appreciate designs that are clean, intuitive, and easy to navigate. </p>



                <a href="#" class="num4">More About Me</a>
